items.name: In Class Quiz 4 and Second Chance to Previous Quizzes

suggestion.title: Avoid using color alone for emphasis
suggestion.description: When emphasizing text, you may use color with sufficient contrast as long as you also apply some other form of emphasis, such as bold or italics. This ensures that screen reader users are aware of the text's importance.

suggestion.title: Consider adding headings to your document to create more structure
suggestion.description: If appropriate, add headings to the page to organize the content for sighted and screen reader users. The headings should represent an accurate outline of the content

error.title: Headings should contain text
error.description: Sighted and screen reader users depend on headings to organize the content on the page. Headings should not be empty and should represent an accurate outline of the content

error.title: Image elements should have an "alt" attribute
error.description: Alternative Text (Alt Text) is an alternative (non-visual) way to describe the meaning of an image. Please provide a brief description of the image for a screen reader user. Note: It should not be the image file name.

error.title: Alternative Text should not be the image filename

error.title: Alternative Text is more than the maximum allowed characters
error.description: Alternative Text (Alt Text) is an alternative (non-visual) way to describe the meaning of an image. Please provide a brief description of the image for a screen reader user. Note: It should not be the image file name.

error.title: Multimedia objects should have text equivalents (e.g., transcripts).
error.description: Multimedia objects should be accompanied by a link to a transcript of the content.

suggestion.title: Avoid using styles for document structure
suggestion.description: Bold and Italics are used to emphasize text, whereas headings are used to define the structure of the document. Headings like h1-h6 are extremely useful for non-sighted users to navigate the structure of the page, and formatting a paragraph to just be big or bold, while it might visually look like a heading , does not make it one.
